raw_data.title: AutoCAD
raw_data.description: Designs and develops submittal packages and computer graphics of unique design utilizing various software packages to provide professional and quality control installations of our products. Controls submittal preparation utilizing AutoCAD Electrical and Excel. Prepares computer graphic display pages with point overlays to meet each unique project’s need.  Design animated graphic parts for each H.V.A.C. subsystem. Coordinates the daily workflow of the AutoCAD Operator. Manages all files and graphic data for storage of data and backups.  Synchronizes data between field and office staff.

raw_data.title: Automation Technician
raw_data.description: Installation, commissioning, maintenance, and repair of Honeywell Control Systems. Performs installation, maintenance or repair services, check out and start-up of diverse technologies including HVAC, Fire & Security, Integrated Systems and internet based computer systems. Also possess basic project management and engineering skills to engineer and install small jobs and perform close out tasks to meet customer requirements.

raw_data.title: Engineering
raw_data.description: Designs and prepares technical pneumatic, electrical, and DDC automatic temperature control drawings from plans and specifications utilizing AutoCAD; coordinates design with Project Managers input until project completion.  Creates, maintains and designs detailed mechanical ATC drawings using Auto CAD equipment and software to meet customer specifications.  Provides routine information and support to field questions, analyzes product field failures and recommends remediation.  Troubleshoots and resolves any issues that arise between ATC drawings created and conditions found out in the field.  Coordinates the daily workflow of the AutoCAD drafters.

raw_data.title: Field Engineer
raw_data.description: Directs and manages multiple projects and project teams for the installation of new building control systems and retrofit projects.  Ensures all projects are completed on time and at the lowest installed cost, while meeting the engineer specifications and customer requirements.  Develops project schedules and executes according to plan for assigned projects.  Supervises the electrical subcontractors and provides daily direction and communication to ensure the project installation is performed in a timely, efficient and knowledgeable manner.  Monitors the quality and quantity of work of subcontractors and provides feedback when necessary. Oversees and coordinates assigned project schedules, materials, parts, supplies, through communication with Electrical Subcontractors, engineers, programmers and office personnel.  Compiles and analyzes statistical reports.  Holds project management meetings; respond to questions regarding schedules, status of PASCO’s scope of work from general contractors, contractors, sub contractors. Makes recommendations regarding any design, installation and or operation issues regarding assigned or unassigned projects to Pasco Management in a timely fashion to allow as much opportunity to mitigate said issues in a satisfactory manner. Coordinates with all field personnel and customers in the resolution of day-to-day field project management and operational problems. Develops and maintains viable long-term relationships with customers, prime contractors, and subcontractors. Responds to customer questions and complaints.  Answers questions on Pasco products and services. Installs and verifies DDC programming and graphics, including individual point verification, control loop operation of each controlled device, and documentation of verification. Prepares various reports including, but not limited to, daily documentation of work performed, completed or outstanding on all assigned projects.  These reports include notes, memos, emails, documented conversations.  Summarizes weekly contractor & subcontractor activity and job status.

raw_data.title: Programmer
raw_data.description: Follows specifications to develop and write computer programs for the entire logic and operation of building automation systems.  Tests and documents modifications and writes Sequence of Operations.   Provides technical support and problem resolution.  Develops and writes computer programs according to specifications for the logic and operation of building automation systems.  Interfaces with the graphics department to ensure graphics accurately represent the equipment being controlled and the sequence of operation.  Writes installation and operational procedures and wiring diagrams.  Provides technical support and problem resolution for installation, network, and software application problems.  Confers with users to diagnose problems and define change requirements. Tests new or modified products by running it to ensure that the instructions are correct and that the program produces the desired outcome.  Analyzes reasons for failure, and revises assigned programs, diagrams, coding, and/or procedures as necessary.  Bench tests field problems and advises information to the factory if problem cannot be resolved in house. Manages phone system and building security card access.
